Okay, "yaar"! Here's a standard .gitignore file that's suitable for most Node.js projects, including yours in Devrukh:

# General Node.js
node_modules
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml
.env

# Logs and temporary files
logs
*.log
*.tmp
temp
tmp

# Editor and IDE specific files
.vscode/
.idea/
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.swp       # Vim swap files
*.swo       # Vim swap files
*.asv       # Autosave files (various editors)
Emacs.d/    # Emacs directory

# Build output
build
dist

# Dependency caches
npm-cache
yarn-cache
pnpm-store

# Optional: Ignore debug output
debug.log

# Optional: Ignore system files (usually hidden)
.DS_Store      # macOS
Thumbs.db     # Windows

# Optional: Ignore coverage reports
coverage

# Optional: Ignore bundled dependencies (if you have any)
bundle/

# Optional: Ignore any files you specifically don't want to track
# my-secret-file.txt